  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hospice Plett - relief of suffering in townships</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIV, TB and chronic diseases have overburdened a developing public health service in South Africa. In the townships of Plettenberg Bay, our team go door to door, serving as an extension of the clinics regarding help with medication adherence, hunger interventions, access to welfare and palliative care.

In order to do this for our population of over 70,000 affected by joblessness, poverty and lack of education, we need to raise R700,000.00 per year over and above Department of Health subsidies</narrative>
  </description>
